cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

The paper introduces a framework for large-scale machine learning using kernel approximates, which is a topic closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification tasks, which fall under computer vision (cs.CV). The algorithm used in the paper involves matrix computations, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper introduces a new architecture of learning that works analogously to neural networks, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
